Class Description
ArchiveConsole  
AutomationConsole
The AutomationConsole class is meant to control a robot to manipulate a physical collection of CDs.
BinaryTree
The BinaryTree can hold a single root Node.
BinaryTree.Node  
Bubble
Bubble.sort(ArrayList) uses the bubble sorting algorithm to arrange the array by an element's Title variable in ascending order.
CDRecord
The CDRecord class is used to store data corresponding to a specific CD.
CDRecordTableModel
The CDRecordTableModel class provides a tableModel format that allows CDRecord data to be stored in a table.
ChatClientUI
The ChatClientUI class is a test class to learn to use sockets to send messages.
Client
The Client class can be implemented inside another class to provide message sending over sockets.
ErrorWindow
The ErrorWindow class is a simple popup window that can be called by the main application.
Insertion
Insertion.sort(ArrayList) uses the insertion sorting algorithm to arrange the array by an element's Author variable in ascending order.
LinkedList
The LinkedList class is a doubly linked list that holds pointers to a head and a tail node.
LinkedList.Node  
MessageListener
The MessageListener interface contains 1 function that must be overridden.
MessageSender
The MessageSender interface contains 1 function that must be overridden.
RecordStorage
The RecordStorage class contains 2 methods used to read and write the CDRecords to a file.
Selection
Selection.sort(ArrayList) uses the selection sorting algorithm to arrange the array by an element's Barcode variable in ascending order.
Server
The Server class is a runnable class with no GUI.
